  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Solution Architect (IT Systems)",
  "description": "<p><br />Our Client is an established company in Singapore, who is seeking to recruit a Solution Architect (IT Systems).</p><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Solution Architect (IT Systems)</strong></u></p><p><br /></p><p>As a Solution Architect, you will help clients to manage the demands of fast-moving business environments. We expect you to have a strong interest in technology and ability to drive innovation with creative solutions. You should have a broad expertise and proven experience in various areas such as web, mobile, Cloud, emerging technologies and services.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>· Provide technical leadership, working with clients to create digital solutions that solve challenges in innovative ways while still integrating with the existing technology landscape.</p><p>· Analyse the solution, prioritize, develop strategy, identify target solution and derive actions list to meet personal and company objectives.</p><p>· Develop and communicate the detailed technology architecture and implementation strategy for a solution to the project team.</p><p>· Lead technical teams through the design and development of complex transactional systems.</p><p>· Lead large-scale system integration, providing both oversight and hands on contributions to the software design, development, and integration.</p><p>· Resolve integration and interfacing issues between various back-end systems. Optimise application performance, scalability and security.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Basic Qualifications</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>Must Have:</p><p>· Minimum of bachelor’s degree or equivalent.</p><p>· 10+ years of enterprise computing experience, including 5-8 years of application and technical architecture credentials.</p><p>· Minimum 5 years of successful credential in large scale solution (Over 5MM).</p><p></p><p>Personal Attributes</p><p>· Driven, Self-Motivated, Proactive and Resilient</p><p>· Able to manage multiple opportunities with tight timelines.</p><p>· Very Confident, Compose and experience in managing client relationship and expectation.</p><p>· Team Player, Self-Learned, Independent, Resourceful.</p><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Desirable Certifications</strong></u></p><p><br /></p><p>· The Open Group TOGAF 9 Certification</p><p>· Any other equivalent industry standard architect certification</p><p><br /></p><p>JJ Consulting Services</p><p>EA Licence No.: 12C6207</p>",
